Unitech Unit Harsil’s Bond Rating Cut to ‘Default’ by Brickwork

-- B y   P o o j a   T h a k u r
-- 
2011-10-14T07:49:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/unitech-unit-harsil-s-bond-rating-cut-to-default-by-brickwork.html
Unitech Ltd. (UT) ’s unit Harsil Projects
Pvt. had the rating on its 2.5 billion rupee non-convertible
bond issue cut to a level that signals default or a risk of
default, from stable, by Brickwork Ratings. The rating was
lowered to “BWR D” from “BWR BB,” according to a statement
from the rating agency today.  The outstanding amount on the bond issue stands at 2
billion rupees, the agency said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pooja Thakur in Mumbai at 
 pthakur@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
